      "content": "Yes, you should definitely try the RICE method for a few days. However, if the pain and swelling don't improve, you might want to consider icing it more frequently and applying a cold pack for 15-20 minutes every hour. Also, try to keep your ankle elevated as much as possible. If the pain persists or worsens, you should definitely see a doctor to rule out a fracture. Remember, sometimes injuries need a bit more attention than just the RICE method.",
